oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Travel Card, S. S. Baltic
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Travel card for the S. S. Baltic. The card was for seat fifty-six in berth one. It instructed the owner that they were allocated second sitting for "mess." There are a list of names and numbers on the reverse of the card.
The S.S. Baltic was the ship that transported SSU 558 from the United States to Europe.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Robert Frank Hodge World War I Papers, 1914-1919
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: American Field Service; World War, 1914-1918
